  "body":"Instead of adding classes to extract the css. Maybe we can add functions so we don't have to think about classes? E.g. we could have a function in styles +sidebar. We would reference it here as `style/+sidebar`.\r\n\r\nIf we use styles or classes it wouldn't matter. We can swap the implementation there, e.g.\r\n```clojure\r\n(defn +sidebar [attrs]\r\n  (update attrs :style merge {:padding 0 :margin 0 :list-style-type \"none\"}))\r\n\r\n(defn +sidebar [attrs]\r\n  (update attrs :class (partial str \" \") \"left-sidebar\"))\r\n```\r\n\r\nWith `carve` in #55 we can remove unused style functions and keep styles.cljs small. What do you think?",
